<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A man burst into a birthday party and opened fire with a gun, killing his estranged wife and three other women while seriously wounding two other people, authorities said Monday. <PERSON> Raymundo </PERSON> <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> was arrested without resistance outside his father's apartment, authorities and witnesses said. He was held without bail for investigation of murder and of attempted murder. <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> <PERSON> Delia </PERSON> <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> was celebrating her 27th birthday with about 20 family members and friends late Sunday when her estranged husband burst in and began shooting a handgun, investigators said. <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> fell dead, as did <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> <PERSON> Garcia </PERSON>, 65, <PERSON> Leticia </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Dipp </PERSON>, 46, and <PERSON> Francisca </PERSON> <PERSON> Arizpe </PERSON>, 62, said coroner's spokesman <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Dambacher </PERSON>. `` I hid behind a cabinet when the man came in and started shooting,'' said 12-year-old <PERSON> Francisco </PERSON> <PERSON> Amazcua </PERSON>. `` I saw people fall to the floor. After he left, I ran into the bedroom and hid under the bed with two other kids.'' An unidentified woman was listed in critical condition at County-USC Medical Center with gunshot wounds to the head, and a man with a bullet wound in the abdomen was in serious condition, <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> sheriff's investigators said. <PERSON> Partygoer </PERSON> <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON> <PERSON> Amezcua </PERSON> said someone telephoned <PERSON> Maria </PERSON>'s apartment about 11 p.m. Sunday to warn partygoers that <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON>, 26, was on his way. <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> telephoned the 911 emergency line and said her husband was coming to kill her, he said. The 911 operator told <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> to call back when <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> arrived, the partygoer said. Minutes later, <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> invaded the party carrying a gun, said <PERSON> Amezcua </PERSON>. The Sheriff's Department confirmed someone called the <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> station prior to the shooting, but said it was unable to give details about the conversation until the tape is located and transcribed. `` He had a very bad temper. They used to fight a lot,'' said <PERSON> Beatrice </PERSON> <PERSON> Palacios </PERSON>, 27, a longtime friend of the couple. The couple separated for about a year and <PERSON> Navarro </PERSON> has been despondent about the breakup, friends said.
