<HEAD>Helmsley Bodyguard Found at Jury's Hotel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 One of <PERSON> Leona </PERSON> <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>'s bodyguards was found in the hotel where the jurors in her tax evasion trial were sequestered and rode the elevator with one juror, according to a report today. But there was `` an innocent explanation and both the government and court are satisfied,'' Assistant <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> DeVita </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION>. The 12-member jury in <PERSON> Leona </PERSON> <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>'s tax evasion and extortion trial was heading into a fourth day of deliberations today. Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, 69, is charged with evading $ 1.2 million in federal taxes by charging personal expenses, including renovations at her <LOCATION> Connecticut </LOCATION> mansion, to her businesses. <PERSON> DeVita </PERSON> and defense attorney <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> Feffer </PERSON> would not say why the unnamed bodyguard was in the hotel Friday night. In court papers, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Court Judge <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Walker </PERSON> told <PERSON> Feffer </PERSON> to `` convey to his client to tell her people to stay out of the hotel.'' `` Needless to say, this is not a Helmsley hotel,'' <PERSON> Walker </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Leona </PERSON> <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON> and her husband <PERSON> Harry </PERSON> are among the biggest owners of hotels and other real estate in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. The judge said a federal marshal was escorting a juror back to her hotel room after dinner Friday when one of Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>'s security guards got on the same elevator The marshal purposely pushed the elevator button for the wrong floor so the guard would not know which floor the juror was staying on, according to the judge in the transcript. The juror, misunderstanding the situation, pushed the correct button. However, the juror and the guard got off the elevator on different floors. `` If the <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON> security people think they are doing their client a favor by investigating where the jurors are, the rooms the jurors are staying in or what floor the jurors are staying in or a particular hotel, they are not,'' <PERSON> Walker </PERSON> said. Two Helmsley guards appeared before the judge, but the transcript of the hearing, including the identity of the guard in question, was sealed.
