<HEAD>Couple Claims Richest Lotto Prize to a Single Winner in Illinois</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A suburban couple came forward today to claim a $ 42 million Lotto jackpot, the richest prize to a single-ticket winner in <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> State Lottery history. <PERSON> William </PERSON> and <PERSON> Kathleen </PERSON> <PERSON> Madigan </PERSON>, who formed the <LOCATION> Madigan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Partnership </LOCATION> to claim the prize, will receive 20 annual payments of $ 2.1 million, officials said at a news conference. The Madigans, who live in Hometown, a southern suburb of <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, bought their ticket for Saturday's Lotto drawing at a White Hen Pantry in suburban <LOCATION> Oak </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lawn </LOCATION>. The convenience store will receive $ 420,000, 1 percent of their winnings, lottery officials said. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Wittkowski </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> printer who was a 1984 Lotto winner, held the previous state single-jackpot record of $ 40 million. The state's biggest jackpot ever was $ 69.9 million for the April 15 drawing this year, but the cash in that grand-prize pool was divided four ways. The winner of the largest undivided lottery prize in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was <PERSON> Sheelah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Winter </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Springs </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, who won $ 55.16 million in the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> lottery on Sept. 3, 1988. Players in the Illinois Lottery select six numbers from 1 to 54. A $ 1 ticket buys two plays. The winning numbers drawn Saturday night were 6, 9, 33, 40, 51, 54.
