<HEAD>Police Shooting Sparks Looting, Rioting</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MELANIE BURNEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>VINELAND, N.J., (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Merchants boarded up storefronts and swept up broken glass Tuesday after a night of vandalism and looting sparked by the fatal police shooting of a black man. Leaders of this city of 54,000 people about 40 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> moved to prevent another night of violence. <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Clark </PERSON>, president of the local chapter of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> for the Advancement of Colored People, met with Mayor <PERSON> Harry </PERSON> <PERSON> Curley </PERSON> to try to defuse racial tensions that escalated into rioting Monday night by nearly 200 people on the city's main street and the arrest of 23 people. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, religious and community leaders met with reporters, and called for continued efforts to root out racism in the wake of the fatal shooting of a black teen-ager by white youths last week. In a separate statement, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> called on New Yorkers to pray `` that we will make this moment of shame a time for honesty and renewal.'' Police said the gang in the borough of <LOCATION> Brooklyn </LOCATION> attacked four black youths because they believed the four were going to visit a young woman who had spurned one of the gang members. <PERSON> Yusef </PERSON> <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON>, 16, was killed. The <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> violence followed Sunday's shooting of <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, 26. About 40 businesses and 20 cars were damaged by rocks and bottles, most of them along a mile-long stretch, police said. Four people were injured. Damage was estimated at $ 75,000 to $ 100,000 for broken windows, and officials were still trying to gauge losses from looting, city spokesman <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON>