<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> trade deficit narrowed to $ 27.7 billion in the second quarter, the best showing in more than four years, as a record level of exports overcame a big surge in the nation's foreign oil bill, the government says. The <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said Monday the 2.3 percent drop in the trade deficit during the April-June period marked the second consecutive quarterly decline. But economists warned that the deficit may be growing again in the second half of the year.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Debt-burdened <ORGANIZATION> Resorts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> says it has stopped stopped paying interest to bondholders, and Resorts officials indicate it will take longer than expected to turn around the troubled hotel-casino company. `` It has become clear that Resorts is a much bigger challenge than we anticipated,'' said company owner and Chairman <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON> in a letter to bondholders of Resorts and its subsidiaries. The letter was made public Monday.
