<HEAD>Farm Groups Split Over Soybean Emergency Order</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: ``Darl'' in 7th graf is cq.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN M. DOYLE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The debate continues over whether the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> should have ordered the emergency liquidation of July soybean futures contracts. `` It's becoming more and more evident that the cost of this liquidation was all put on the back of the producers,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farm </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Federation </ORGANIZATION>. But <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Mennel </PERSON>, an <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> representative of the Millers' National Federation, said he thought the <ORGANIZATION> BOT </ORGANIZATION> `` did a magnificent job of moving very rapidly to stop something that could have gone horribly wrong. Mennel and <PERSON> White </PERSON> were among more than a score of farmers, ranchers, exporters, grain dealers and elevator operators who debated the soybean emergency action Monday at a meeting of the <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trading </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>'s agricultural advisory committee. Last month, the <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> issued an emergency order requiring traders to reduce their holdings in soybean futures contracts. The move brought howls of protest from farmers and traders, who saw the value of their futures holdings plummet after the order caused wild swings in soybean prices. The <ORGANIZATION> CBOT </ORGANIZATION>'s action was taken after a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> affiliate of the Italian grain conglomerate <ORGANIZATION> Ferruzzi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Finanziaria </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SPA </ORGANIZATION> refused to