<HEAD>Unisys Names Unruh President, Putting Him In Line For Top Job</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLUE BELL, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> officials hope a new president can turn around the company's recent drop in earnings by focusing on network computer systems and software. <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION>' board of directors Monday promoted <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Unruh </PERSON> to president and chief operating officer, putting him in line to succeed the 63-year-old chairman and chief executive, <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Blumenthal </PERSON>. Before <PERSON> Unruh </PERSON>'s promotion, the company had no president and chief operating officer. `` His top priority will be to strengthen the company's financial position by improving profitability and cash flow and to continue the company's thrust into the faster-growing markets of distributed network computing systems and software and services,'' <PERSON> Blumenthal </PERSON> said in a news release. <PERSON> Unruh </PERSON> will handle all computer business except defense sales. <PERSON> Unruh </PERSON>, 48, beat out <PERSON> Curtis </PERSON> <PERSON> Hessler </PERSON>, 45, for the No. 2 job at the computer giant. <PERSON> Hessler </PERSON>, who worked with <PERSON> Blumenthal </PERSON> when he was <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> secretary in the <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> administration, and <PERSON> Unruh </PERSON>, a former Burroughs executive, were viewed as the two candidates to take over when <PERSON> Blumenthal </PERSON> retires. <PERSON> Blumenthal </PERSON>, who engineered <PERSON> Burrough </PERSON>'s takeover of <LOCATION> Sperry </LOCATION> to form <ORGANIZATION> Unisys </ORGANIZATION>, has indicated he may step down in two years. <PERSON> Hessler </PERSON> was promoted from executive vice president to vice chairman. <PERSON> Hessler </PERSON>'s duties still include chief financial officer and head of the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Systems </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>. `` <PERSON> C